```diff
if (config.notarize) {
  notarize = config.notarize;
  notary_user = config.notary_user;
  notary_password = config.notary_password;
}
```

This change is missing the necessary curly braces `{}` around the block of code. As a result, only the first line `notarize = config.notarize;` will be executed when `config.notarize` is true. The subsequent lines `notary_user = config.notary_user;` and `notary_password = config.notary_password;` will not be part of the conditional block and will always execute, regardless of whether `config.notarize` is true or false. This could lead to unexpected behavior in the code.
